history.text: hi
what do you like about the movie?
I like that it was written about Tina Fey
I like that it is directed by Mark Waters, I am a big fan of his.
I meant written BY Tina Fey, sorry. I also like that Amanda Seyfried was in it, I've always really identified with her.
Lindsay Lohan also adds to the show
I think it was a really defining movie of the time. I can't believe 2004 was so long ago now, but it's very nostalgic for me and others my age.
I liked Rotten Tomatoes
I wonder how much the movie was like the book it was based on, Queen Bees and Wannabees.
Do you agree with the Rotten Tomatoes rating?
No, i htink it was very good and should have been rated much highrt
Do you generally enjoy movies about high school?
transitioning form homeschooling must have been hard for Cady
the transition from Africa to illinois must have been hard as well
It especially must have been hard since the Plastics AND Janis both took such an immediate interest in Cady; they basically forced her to be in the middle of a situation she wasn't ready for.
It's interesting to me that the movie is set in Evanston, Illinois. I didn't remember that; i'm from Illinois originally so that's funny to me!
I agree, what a hard poisiton to be in
and Regina acted so horrible too
You've got to have a little sympathy for her when she gets hit by the bus though!
hahha true
I like that they all confess their faults though
That scene is so great and really funny! But it's understandable that Janis takes the opportunity to rat Cady out because the Plastics are still so awful to her.
haha yes she just wanted revenge
Which she immediately got when Regina got hit by the bus.
but you are right poor regina getting hit by a bus and breaking her spine was no fun
I like that Cady takes the blame for the burnt book
I agree! And I like that she doesn't just take the title of prom queen and instead breaks the tiara and shares it with everyone.
yes, and reaches a truce with the Plastics
Not only does she reconcile with the Plastics, but she does so with Janis, Damian, and Aaron, too. It's such a good ending.
I agree the ending was great
She even joined the Mathletes and returned to her old self, which was nice to see.
